<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="1088" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1088">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/4004.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Consul General <persName type="to">Hanna</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-30">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 30, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Consul, Matamoros, telegraphs Department that it is impossible to assist
                            Americans at Saltillo. Department authorizes you to send such special
                            messengers as may be necessary in your judgment to extend protection to
                            Americans in Saltillo. Department regrets that it has no accurate
                            information regarding conditions at Saltillo and therefore must entrust
                            to your accurate knowledge of situation as it exists to-day the measure
                            of relief which should be extended.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>